```

**What it actually does** (matches CLAUDE.md description exactly):
- Floating bottom-right FAB button (`buildFab()`, line 755) with
  speech-bubble SVG + "AI" badge
- Slide-out chat panel with header, body, composer textarea
- Loads Gemma 3 1B ONNX (`onnx-community/gemma-3-1b-it-ONNX`, ~600 MB, q4
  quantized) via `@huggingface/transformers@3` from jsDelivr CDN
- WebGPU runtime; if `navigator.gpu` missing → graceful "not supported"
  message
- First-load progress bar with percentage
- Reads `.lang-content.active` `.innerText` at send-time, truncates to
  12,000 chars, stuffs into system prompt — so the assistant always answers
  about the lesson currently shown
- i18n in EN/HK/TW/CN (titles, prompts, errors); MutationObserver keeps it
  in sync when the user switches language
- Streaming output, chat history (max 6 turns), markdown rendering, mermaid
  chart support with diagram/source toggle
- Clear-conversation and close buttons
- Browser-side caching via transformers.js IndexedDB (no server roundtrip
  after first load)

