1. **`Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration` not exported by transformers.js v4 ESM
  build** — if the import returns `undefined`, the load button will throw
  `TypeError: Class extends value undefined`. If so, we'll need the exact
  export name from the v4 release notes.
2. **Text-only input rejected by processor** — the HF sample passes
  image+audio. If `processor(prompt, null, null, ...)` complains about
  missing modalities, we may need to pass empty arrays or use a text-only
  `processor.apply_chat_template({ tokenize: true, return_tensors: true })`
  path.
3. **3.1 GB > IndexedDB quota** on some browsers (Firefox default ~10% of
  disk; Chrome usually fine). User will see a quota error mid-download.
4. **Generation throughput** on E2B is roughly 2-5× slower than Gemma 3 1B
  on the same GPU.

